headline: Rampant AI Demand for Memory Is Fueling a Growing Chip Crisis
summary: Since the start of 2026, Tesla Inc., Apple Inc. and a dozen other major corporations have signaled that the shortage of DRAM, or dynamic random access memory — the fundamental building block of almost all technology — will constrain production.  Cook warned it will compress iPhone margins.  Micron Technology Inc. called the bottleneck “unprecedented.”

headline: Apple Scrutiny On News And Siri AI Delays Tests Investor Expectations
summary: Apple is under investigation by the U.S. Federal Trade Commission over allegations of political bias in its Apple News service. The probe focuses on claims that Apple News favors certain political viewpoints, raising regulatory and legal questions for the company. Separately, Apple is experiencing delays to planned AI upgrades for its Siri virtual assistant due to technical challenges. Both developments have arrived at the same time, increasing scrutiny of Apple’s role in media distribution...
